{"word":"ἀσκητός","slug":"ἀσκητός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀσκητός</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀσκέω'><el>ἀσκέω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>curiously wrought</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>: <i>adorned</i>, <el>πέπλωι</el> with a robe, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to be acquired by practice</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>of persons, <i>practised</i> in a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}